title: Amethyst Crystal
description: A cluster of amethyst crystals, showcasing various shades of purple and a shiny, crystalline structure.

title: White Mineral Cluster
description: A cluster of white mineral crystals, resembling a fluffy or cloud-like formation. The crystals are irregularly shaped and vary in size, giving the piece a textured appearance.

description: A piece of purple fluorite crystal, showcasing its characteristic translucent purple color with layered formations and some black inclusions.

title: Crystalline Structure

title: Rock Sample

title: Rock Sample

title: Pile of Rocks
description: A small pile of irregularly shaped rocks with a rough texture. The rocks have a mix of earthy colors, including browns and greens, and some patches of moss or lichen are visible on their surfaces.

title: Blue Crystal Geode
description: A geode with a rough exterior and a hollow interior filled with sparkling blue crystals. The crystals are well-formed and reflect light, creating a shimmering effect.

title: Obsidian Rock
description: A cluster of obsidian, a naturally occurring volcanic glass, characterized by its shiny black surface and sharp edges. The rock appears jagged and irregular, with some areas reflecting light.

title: Obsidian Rock
description: A piece of obsidian, a naturally occurring volcanic glass, characterized by its shiny black surface and sharp edges. The rock has a jagged, layered appearance, indicating its formation from rapidly cooled lava.
